{"repository": {"owner": {"login": "WordPress"}, "name": "gutenberg", "forkCount": 2298, "stargazerCount": 6652, "createdAt": "2017-02-03T19:34:19Z", "updatedAt": "2021-03-11T03:54:07Z", "repositoryTopics": {"edges": [{"node": {"topic": {"name": "wordpress"}}}, {"node": {"topic": {"name": "gutenberg"}}}, {"node": {"topic": {"name": "wordpress-plugin"}}}]}, "languages": {"edges": [{"node": {"name": "JavaScript"}}, {"node": {"name": "Shell"}}, {"node": {"name": "PHP"}}, {"node": {"name": "SCSS"}}, {"node": {"name": "CSS"}}, {"node": {"name": "HTML"}}, {"node": {"name": "Ruby"}}, {"node": {"name": "Kotlin"}}, {"node": {"name": "Java"}}, {"node": {"name": "Swift"}}, {"node": {"name": "Objective-C"}}, {"node": {"name": "Starlark"}}, {"node": {"name": "TypeScript"}}, {"node": {"name": "Mustache"}}]}, "primaryLanguage": {"name": "JavaScript"}}, "id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1NzAwMTE4MjY=", "number": 20417, "author": {"login": "mapk"}, "title": "Heading's Advanced metabox content order is not persistent", "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nBased on an issue recorded here: https://wordpress.org/support/topic/ordering-of-advanced-options-in-editor/\r\n\r\nThe Advanced metabox shows two options for a Heading block: CSS class and an HTML anchor. These two options switch visual order if the user converts a Paragraph block to a Heading block.\r\n\r\n**To reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Add a Heading block.\r\n2. Open the Advanced metabox and note the order of options: HTML anchor then CSS Class.\r\n3. Add a Paragraph block with content.\r\n4. Convert that block to a Heading block. \r\n5. Open the Advanced metabox and note the order of options: CSS Class then HTML anchor.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nThe content order should remain the same regardless of how the Heading block was created.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n\r\n**Creating a Heading block**\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2020-02-24 at 9 31 46 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/617986/75176557-38e32380-56e9-11ea-976b-aebc211348b6.png)\r\n\r\n**Converting a Paragraph block to a Heading block**\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2020-02-24 at 9 32 25 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/617986/75176579-426c8b80-56e9-11ea-8ec4-c26f4b877644.png)\r\n", "bodyHTML": "<p><strong>Describe the bug</strong><br>\nBased on an issue recorded here: <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/ordering-of-advanced-options-in-editor/\">https://wordpress.org/support/topic/ordering-of-advanced-options-in-editor/</a></p>\n<p>The Advanced metabox shows two options for a Heading block: CSS class and an HTML anchor. These two options switch visual order if the user converts a Paragraph block to a Heading block.</p>\n<p><strong>To reproduce</strong><br>\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Add a Heading block.</li>\n<li>Open the Advanced metabox and note the order of options: HTML anchor then CSS Class.</li>\n<li>Add a Paragraph block with content.</li>\n<li>Convert that block to a Heading block.</li>\n<li>Open the Advanced metabox and note the order of options: CSS Class then HTML anchor.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Expected behavior</strong><br>\nThe content order should remain the same regardless of how the Heading block was created.</p>\n<p><strong>Screenshots</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Creating a Heading block</strong></p>\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/617986/75176557-38e32380-56e9-11ea-976b-aebc211348b6.png\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/617986/75176557-38e32380-56e9-11ea-976b-aebc211348b6.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-02-24 at 9 31 46 AM\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a></p>\n<p><strong>Converting a Paragraph block to a Heading block</strong></p>\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/617986/75176579-426c8b80-56e9-11ea-8ec4-c26f4b877644.png\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/617986/75176579-426c8b80-56e9-11ea-8ec4-c26f4b877644.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-02-24 at 9 32 25 AM\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a></p>", "bodyText": "Describe the bug\nBased on an issue recorded here: https://wordpress.org/support/topic/ordering-of-advanced-options-in-editor/\nThe Advanced metabox shows two options for a Heading block: CSS class and an HTML anchor. These two options switch visual order if the user converts a Paragraph block to a Heading block.\nTo reproduce\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n\nAdd a Heading block.\nOpen the Advanced metabox and note the order of options: HTML anchor then CSS Class.\nAdd a Paragraph block with content.\nConvert that block to a Heading block.\nOpen the Advanced metabox and note the order of options: CSS Class then HTML anchor.\n\nExpected behavior\nThe content order should remain the same regardless of how the Heading block was created.\nScreenshots\nCreating a Heading block\n\nConverting a Paragraph block to a Heading block", "assignees": {"edges": []}, "createdAt": "2020-02-24T17:38:05Z", "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-06-16T09:16:54Z", "lastEditedAt": null, "publishedAt": "2020-02-24T17:38:05Z", "comments": {"totalCount": 3, "edges": [{"node": {"id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU5MjY1NDkyOQ==", "author": {"login": "donmhico"}, "body": "Hello @mapk,\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, I can't replicate the issue.\r\n\r\n![Kapture 2020-02-29 at 1 43 39](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5747475/75573562-13169f80-5a98-11ea-951b-fe55c1b587bd.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n", "bodyText": "Hello @mapk,\nUnfortunately, I can't replicate the issue.", "bodyHTML": "<p>Hello <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/mapk/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/mapk\">@mapk</a>,</p>\n<p>Unfortunately, I can't replicate the issue.</p>\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5747475/75573562-